    {
        "SurahNumber": 47,
        "AyahNumber": 10,
        "Tafseer": "\"Have they not traveled through the land and seen how was the end of those before them? Allah destroyed [everything] over them, and for the disbelievers is something comparable.\" (10)\n\nThe Lack of Insight of the Quraysh\n\nThis expresses regret over the blindness and lack of insight of these polytheists—asking: have these people never traveled through the land with the purpose of seeing what was the end of the nations before them, whom Allah destroyed completely! The style of the verse indicates that they did travel, and passed by the settlements of the punished nations in their commercial journeys, but they never looked with warning at those settlements which were once the homes of great nations but are now barren deserts. This points to those nations whose stories have been narrated in the previous Surahs.\n\n'and for the disbelievers is something comparable'—it states: for the disbelievers are their examples—meaning when they faced this end as a retribution for their disbelief and denial, there is no reason why these (the Quraysh) should face any different end if they adopt their way. The law of Allah is the same for everyone... under verse 3: 'Thus does Allah present to the people their parables' above, have a look at what we wrote."
