    {
        "SurahNumber": 47,
        "AyahNumber": 12,
        "Tafseer": "\"Indeed, Allah will admit those who have believed and done righteous deeds to gardens beneath which rivers flow, but those who disbelieve enjoy themselves and eat as cattle eat, and the Fire will be a residence for them.\" (12)\n\nThis is a further explanation of the believers' reward and the disbelievers' deeds going to waste, and is a reply to the doubt: if the disbelievers' deeds hold no status, why are they dandanate in this world? It states: Allah Almighty will admit the believers to gardens beneath which rivers flow; as for these disbelievers, their residence is the Fire. The respite they have received to eat and live in this world is no good thing. Their eating and drinking is like that of cattle. They are devoid of intellect and of the consciousness of those duties which Allah's blessings impose upon them; for this reason, let them enjoy these blessings for a few days, but they will become a cause of ruin for them, and their final residence will be Hell."
