    {
        "SurahNumber": 47,
        "AyahNumber": 13,
        "Tafseer": "\"And how many a city was stronger than your city [i.e., Makkah] which drove you out? We destroyed them, and there was no helper for them.\" (13)\n\nThat is: let no one remain in the misconception that today the Quraysh enjoy great power, and when they have turned out the Prophet and his companions from Makkah, who can subdue such strong people! It states: how many cities were greater than this in strength and power, but Allah destroyed them, and there was no helper for them. This points to 'Aad, Thamud, etc. whose stories have been narrated, and of whose power and glory the Quraysh had full acknowledgment. 'and there was no helper for them' negates the help of their worldly numbers of which they were proud, and also of those assumed partners whom they considered their shields against God."
